.TH "ddp-bind" "1" "04 March 2020" "CZ.NIC" "@PROJECT_NAME@ @PROJECT_VERSION@"
.SH NAME
.B ddp-bind
\- Python script that wraps around
.B dp-dpdk
wrapper. DNS traffic monitoring probe with DPDK backend.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ddp-bind
[-i <INTERFACE> | -p <PCAP>] [-r] [-l <LOGFILE>] [-h]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ddp-bind
is a Python script that wraps around
.B dp-dpdk
wrapper. It simplifies usage of the
.B dp-dpdk
application with DPDK backend by automatically binding given network interfaces to DPDK drivers
before running the application. When the application exits the wrapper automatically binds
the network interfaces back to their original drivers.
.SH OPTIONS
.B -i <INTERFACE>
Interface name e.g. eth0. Parameter can repeat.
.TP
.B -p <PCAP>
Input PCAP file. Parameter can repeat.
.TP
.B -r
Indicates RAW PCAPs as input. Can't be used together with -i parameter.
.TP
.B -l <LOGFILE>
Redirects probe's logs to LOGFILE instead of standard output.
.TP
.B -h
Print help message.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dp-dpdk (1),
.BR dns-probe-dpdk (1)
